OL,3,CAsda fined #0.5m over out-of-date food
OL,4,Cat supermarket
OL,6,FThe prosecution was brought by
OL,7,FBarnsley Council's Trading Standards
OL,8,Fafter a series of visits to the Old
OL,9,FMill Lane store in 2024 found that,
OL,10,Fdespite several warnings, it was
OL,11,Fcontinuing to display out -of-date
OL,12,Ffood items for sale which collectively
OL,13,Ftotalled almost 700 days past their
OL,14,Fuse-by-date.
OL,16,FAll out-of-date food products found
OL,17,Fduring these visits were seized by the
OL,18,FTrading Standards team, who informed
OL,19,Fthe store that follow-up visits would
OL,20,Ftake place to ensure compliance with
OL,21,Fthis important food safety issue.
